cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AR 

The paper proposes two case studies that involve the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques for building information modeling and classification. The first case study involves the use of deep learning techniques to extract visual information of buildings from satellite/street view images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The second case study involves the use of automated deep learning-based procedures for identifying soft-story buildings from street view images, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed framework and statistical tool for building information modeling involve the use of graph theory and spatial analysis, which fall under the graphics (cs.GR) and augmented reality (cs.AR) sub-categories.
